## Binary Specifications

### Binary Composition

```yaml
Total Size: 400-500MB compressed

Breakdown:
  Core CASCI Engine: 50MB
    - HTTP/WebSocket server
    - Database abstraction
    - Queue management
    - Scheduler
    - Resource manager
    
  Plugin Compatibility (3000+ plugins): 200MB
    - Build tool orchestration
    - SCM integration
    - Testing frameworks
    - Deployment logic
    - Notification handlers
    - Artifact management
    - Cloud integrations
    - Security scanning
    - Monitoring/metrics
    - Pipeline logic
    
  Web UI: 80MB
    - Complete dashboard
    - Pipeline visualization
    - Build logs viewer
    - Node management
    - User management
    - Settings interface
    - Real-time updates
    - Mobile responsive
    - 100+ views
    
  Embedded Security Tools: 170MB
    - Trivy (30MB) - Container/code scanning
    - Semgrep (40MB) - SAST analysis
    - Gitleaks (8MB) - Secret detection
    - Syft (25MB) - SBOM generation
    - Grype (20MB) - Vulnerability DB
    - Cosign (15MB) - Signing
    - License scanners (60MB)
    
  Git Implementation: 15MB
    - go-git library
    - Full Git protocol
    - No external Git needed
    
  Jenkins API: 40MB
    - Complete REST API
    - XML job configs
    - CLI compatibility
    - Plugin API stubs
    
  Intelligence Engine: 30MB
    - Project detection rules
    - Pipeline templates
    - Optimization logic
    - Pattern matching
```

### Embedded Components

```go
// Binary embedding strategy
//go:embed ui/dist/*
var webUI embed.FS

//go:embed templates/*
var pipelineTemplates embed.FS

//go:embed scanners/trivy-linux-amd64
//go:embed scanners/trivy-linux-arm64
//go:embed scanners/trivy-darwin-amd64
//go:embed scanners/trivy-darwin-arm64
//go:embed scanners/trivy-windows-amd64.exe
var securityScanners embed.FS

// Multi-architecture support
func getEmbeddedBinary(tool string) []byte {
    platform := runtime.GOOS + "-" + runtime.GOARCH
    return scanners[tool][platform]
}
```

### Build Process

```bash
# Development build
go build -tags dev -o casci ./cmd/casci
# Size: ~600MB (includes debug symbols)

# Production build
CGO_ENABLED=0 go build \
  -ldflags="-s -w -X main.Version=${VERSION}" \
  -tags prod \
  -o casci ./cmd/casci
# Size: ~500MB

# Compressed with UPX
upx --ultra-brute casci
# Final size: 400-450MB

# Per-platform builds
make build-all
# Produces:
#   casci-linux-amd64 (450MB)
#   casci-linux-arm64 (440MB)
#   casci-darwin-amd64 (460MB)
#   casci-darwin-arm64 (450MB)
#   casci-windows-amd64.exe (470MB)
```

