## Deployment Architecture

### Deployment Models

```yaml
Single Node (Development/Small Team):
  - One binary does everything
  - SQLite database
  - Local Docker for builds
  - Perfect for: Startups, personal projects
  - Cost: $0 (existing hardware) or $5/month VPS
  
Small Cluster (Team/SMB):
  - 1 orchestrator node
  - 2-5 build nodes
  - PostgreSQL database
  - Cost: $83/year (Oracle Free + SSDNodes)
  
Medium Cluster (Growing Company):
  - 2 orchestrators (HA)
  - 10-50 build nodes
  - PostgreSQL + Redis
  - Load balancer detected
  - Cost: ~$100-500/month
  
Large Cluster (Enterprise):
  - Multiple orchestrators
  - 100-1000+ build nodes
  - Multi-region deployment
  - Database clustering
  - Cost: Variable based on scale
  
Hybrid (Most Common):
  - Core infrastructure on-premise
  - Burst to cloud for peaks
  - Mix of permanent and hourly nodes
  - User-provided resources
```

### Reference Architecture: $83/year Setup

```yaml
Infrastructure:
  Node 1 - Orchestrator:
    Provider: Oracle Cloud Free Tier
    Specs: 1 vCPU, 1GB RAM (AMD64)
    Role: UI, API, scheduling
    Cost: FREE
    
  Node 2 - Backup/DB:
    Provider: Oracle Cloud Free Tier
    Specs: 1 vCPU, 1GB RAM (AMD64)
    Role: Backup orchestrator, Redis, monitoring
    Cost: FREE
    
  Node 3 - ARM Builder:
    Provider: Oracle Cloud Free Tier
    Specs: 4 vCPU, 24GB RAM (ARM64)
    Role: ARM64 builds
    Cost: FREE
    
  Node 4 - AMD64 Builder:
    Provider: SSDNodes
    Specs: 2 vCPU, 8GB RAM, 160GB SSD
    Role: x86_64 builds
    Cost: $83/year
    
Total: $83/year for complete multi-arch CI/CD
Replaces: $500-5000/month of commercial CI/CD
```

### Network Architecture

```yaml
Network Topology:
  
Public Network:
  - Orchestrator: Public IP, ports 80/443
  - Build nodes: Can be private
  - Git webhooks: Incoming HTTPS
  - Artifact uploads: Outgoing HTTPS
  
Private Network:
  - Node communication: TLS encrypted
  - Database: Private network only
  - Redis: Private network only
  - Build isolation: casci0 interface
  
Security:
  - All communication TLS 1.3
  - Certificate pinning
  - Mutual TLS for nodes
  - Network isolation for builds
  - No internal network access from builds
```

### High Availability

```yaml
HA Configuration:
  
Orchestrator HA:
  - Primary orchestrator (active)
  - Secondary orchestrators (standby)
  - Automatic failover (<30 seconds)
  - Shared nothing architecture
  - Raft consensus for leader election
  
Database HA:
  - Primary: PostgreSQL/MySQL
  - Replicas: 1-3 read replicas
  - Backup: SQLite cache on each node
  - Automatic failover
  - Point-in-time recovery
  
Build Node HA:
  - No single point of failure
  - Automatic job redistribution
  - Health checks every 10 seconds
  - Dead node detection
  - Automatic cleanup
  
Load Balancing:
  - Auto-detected at 10+ nodes
  - Supports: HAProxy, nginx, AWS ELB, etc.
  - Active-active orchestrators
  - Session affinity optional
```

---

## Database Architecture

### Database Design

```yaml
Supported Databases:
  
SQLite (Default):
  - Embedded, zero configuration
  - Good for: <10GB data, <100 users
  - Single file: /var/lib/casci/casci.db
  - Automatic backups
  - Used as cache with remote DB
  
PostgreSQL:
  - Recommended for production
  - Multiple connections supported
  - Read replicas supported
  - Connection pooling
  - SSL/TLS required
  
MySQL/MariaDB:
  - Full support
  - Multiple connections
  - Read replicas
  - UTF8MB4 required
  
Mixed Mode:
  - Multiple database types
  - Example: 3 MariaDB + 1 PostgreSQL
  - Automatic sync between all
  - Failover priority configurable
```

### Schema Overview

```sql
-- Core tables
CREATE TABLE users (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    password_hash VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    api_token VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE,
    is_admin BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE projects (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INTEGER REFERENCES users(id),
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    repository_url TEXT NOT NULL,
    branch VARCHAR(255) DEFAULT 'main',
    pipeline_config JSONB,
    auto_detect BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    UNIQUE(user_id, name)
);

CREATE TABLE builds (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    project_id INTEGER REFERENCES projects(id),
    build_number INTEGER NOT NULL,
    status VARCHAR(50), -- queued, running, success, failed
    trigger VARCHAR(50), -- push, pr, manual, schedule
    commit_sha VARCHAR(40),
    started_at TIMESTAMP,
    finished_at TIMESTAMP,
    log_path TEXT,
    artifacts JSONB,
    UNIQUE(project_id, build_number)
);

CREATE TABLE nodes (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    hostname VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    ip_address INET,
    port INTEGER DEFAULT 8080,
    architecture VARCHAR(50), -- amd64, arm64
    os VARCHAR(50), -- linux, darwin, windows
    role VARCHAR(50), -- orchestrator, builder, hybrid
    capacity JSONB, -- CPU, RAM, disk
    labels JSONB,
    last_heartbeat TIMESTAMP,
    status VARCHAR(50) -- online, offline, draining
);

CREATE TABLE server_settings (
    key VARCHAR(255) PRIMARY KEY,
    value TEXT,
    type VARCHAR(50), -- string, int, bool, json
    category VARCHAR(50),
    updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- Security tables
CREATE TABLE user_credentials (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INTEGER REFERENCES users(id),
    credential_type VARCHAR(50), -- gpg, ssh, signing_cert
    public_key TEXT,
    private_key_encrypted TEXT,
    metadata JSONB,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE project_credentials (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    project_id INTEGER REFERENCES projects(id),
    credential_type VARCHAR(50),
    name VARCHAR(255),
    value_encrypted TEXT,
    UNIQUE(project_id, credential_type, name)
);

-- Cloud/Infrastructure tables
CREATE TABLE cloud_accounts (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INTEGER REFERENCES users(id),
    provider VARCHAR(50), -- aws, gcp, azure, vultr
    account_name VARCHAR(255),
    credentials_encrypted TEXT,
    monthly_budget DECIMAL(10,2),
    current_spend DECIMAL(10,2),
    UNIQUE(user_id, provider, account_name)
);

CREATE TABLE user_nodes (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INTEGER REFERENCES users(id),
    name VARCHAR(255),
    connection_type VARCHAR(50), -- ssh, winrm, docker
    connection_details_encrypted JSONB,
    architecture VARCHAR(50),
    exclusive BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
    UNIQUE(user_id, name)
);

-- Audit tables
CREATE TABLE audit_log (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INTEGER REFERENCES users(id),
    action VARCHAR(255),
    resource_type VARCHAR(50),
    resource_id INTEGER,
    details JSONB,
    ip_address INET,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE build_security_reports (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    build_id INTEGER REFERENCES builds(id),
    scan_type VARCHAR(50), -- vulnerability, license, secrets
    critical_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    high_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    medium_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    low_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    details JSONB,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
```

### Database Operations

```go
type DatabaseManager struct {
    primary   *sql.DB
    replicas  []*sql.DB
    cache     *SqliteCache
    redis     *redis.Client
}

func (dm *DatabaseManager) Query(query string, args ...interface{}) (*sql.Rows, error) {
    // Try primary first
    if dm.primary != nil {
        return dm.primary.Query(query, args...)
    }
    
    // Fallback to replica
    for _, replica := range dm.replicas {
        if rows, err := replica.Query(query, args...); err == nil {
            return rows, nil
        }
    }
    
    // Last resort: SQLite cache
    return dm.cache.Query(query, args...)
}

func (dm *DatabaseManager) Write(query string, args ...interface{}) error {
    // Write to all databases
    var lastErr error
    
    if dm.primary != nil {
        lastErr = dm.primary.Exec(query, args...)
    }
    
    // Async replication to others
    go dm.replicateToAll(query, args...)
    
    return lastErr
}
```

