1-9 Nodes:
  - Single primary orchestrator
  - Primary handles UI/API/scheduling
  - Other nodes are builders
  - Simple architecture

10-49 Nodes:
  - Load balancer detected
  - Secondary orchestrator promoted
  - Active-active orchestrators
  - Improved availability

50-99 Nodes:
  - Regional orchestrators
  - Database clustering
  - Advanced scheduling
  - Monitoring important

100+ Nodes:
  - Full enterprise features
  - Multiple regions
  - Complex scheduling
  - Dedicated monitoring nodes
```

